      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARD ROW (2) was safely held in tougher company last start after losing his position early at Sandown, but prior to that won by a long neck at Sandown (29.91) beating Flying Toxic in a Mix 6/7 on February 12. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Has claims if he runs up to expectations. EAGLE BREAD (4) boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten one length (25.17) behind Bruce at Sale. Expected to be in the finish again. PINK GIN (1) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 2.25 lengths at Healesville in a handy 19.34 beating Rupee Action. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Expected to measure up again. GALLOPING RED (7) cannot be ruled out.",
